WEBVTT


00:00:56.161 --> 00:00:58.581
FINALE

00:01:19.101 --> 00:01:20.102
Do Eun-hyuk.

00:01:23.564 --> 00:01:24.440
Turn around.

00:01:52.718 --> 00:01:53.761
I'm going to Cheongun.

00:01:56.430 --> 00:01:57.389
CHA WOO-SEOK

00:01:59.308 --> 00:02:00.476
HAN SEOL-AH

00:02:13.656 --> 00:02:14.657
POWER OFF

00:02:15.866 --> 00:02:17.743
The phone you are trying to reach
is turned off.

00:02:17.826 --> 00:02:19.161
CALL ENDED

00:02:21.121 --> 00:02:22.957
When Yoon Seung-jae found out

00:02:23.666 --> 00:02:25.709
that Han Seol-ah's men who took out
insurance policies ended up dead,

00:02:26.543 --> 00:02:28.170
he took out a policy himself.

00:02:28.754 --> 00:02:30.297
He wanted to see how you'd react.

00:02:30.923 --> 00:02:32.257
And Do Eun-hyuk encouraged him.

00:02:33.842 --> 00:02:35.886
Do Eun-hyuk's mother sold insurance,

00:02:35.970 --> 00:02:38.138
so he knew a lot about it
from a young age.

00:02:39.515 --> 00:02:44.228
Eun-hyuk said I should take out a policy
to see if you'd accept my proposal.

00:02:45.980 --> 00:02:48.148
I won't use you as bait.

00:02:49.149 --> 00:02:52.528
I'm the only one who can approach them
without raising suspicion.

00:02:52.611 --> 00:02:53.487
I'll do it.

00:02:53.988 --> 00:02:54.822
DO EUN-HYUK

00:02:58.617 --> 00:03:00.411
DO EUN-HYE PRIVATE TUTORING EXPENSES
LIVING EXPENSES

00:03:00.494 --> 00:03:01.996
This isn't over

00:03:03.038 --> 00:03:04.456
until we catch the killer.

00:03:39.575 --> 00:03:40.701
You haven't killed me yet.

00:03:43.912 --> 00:03:44.913
I'm thinking about it.

00:03:46.498 --> 00:03:48.417
You weren't part of the plan.

00:03:53.172 --> 00:03:55.841
How did you know it was me?

00:03:58.719 --> 00:04:01.221
No one could get away
with killing someone on a yacht…

00:04:03.390 --> 00:04:05.934
better than an underwater photographer.

00:04:06.018 --> 00:04:08.270
HAN SEOL-AH

00:04:08.729 --> 00:04:09.813
CHA WOO-SEOK

00:04:12.441 --> 00:04:13.609
Hello?

00:04:14.902 --> 00:04:16.487
If you hadn't seen Kim Yun-ji that day,

00:04:17.529 --> 00:04:18.947
it would've been the perfect crime.

00:04:20.282 --> 00:04:21.116
Right?

00:04:23.327 --> 00:04:26.371
Auctioneers all have a keen eye.

00:04:30.709 --> 00:04:32.044
That woman was just unlucky.

00:04:42.554 --> 00:04:43.639
What is it?

00:04:44.306 --> 00:04:46.809
You could've at least made a sound.
That was creepy.

00:04:46.892 --> 00:04:47.810
Did I scare you?

00:04:47.893 --> 00:04:48.894
I'm sorry.

00:04:49.520 --> 00:04:50.813
It was too suffocating down there.

00:04:55.692 --> 00:04:58.362
I think this is the first time
we've actually talked.

00:05:00.781 --> 00:05:03.659
Do you even talk to anyone here
besides Ms. Han?

00:05:05.119 --> 00:05:07.329
I heard you used to be
an underwater photographer.

00:05:08.747 --> 00:05:10.207
How do you take photos like that?

00:05:11.125 --> 00:05:12.167
For starters,

00:05:13.836 --> 00:05:15.462
you need professional diving equipment,

00:05:15.546 --> 00:05:17.214
and you have to practice diving.

00:05:18.465 --> 00:05:19.675
Diving practice too?

00:05:20.425 --> 00:05:21.635
That sounds hard.

00:05:27.266 --> 00:05:29.601
Where's your studio?

00:05:32.521 --> 00:05:33.522
In Cheongun.

00:06:13.437 --> 00:06:14.313
What's the matter?

00:06:16.773 --> 00:06:18.317
SIU INVESTIGATOR CHA WOO-SEOK

00:06:20.110 --> 00:06:21.028
Aren't you going to answer?

00:06:23.197 --> 00:06:26.325
-Did you see something you shouldn't have?
-Don't come near me.

00:06:41.173 --> 00:06:44.218
It's her fault for doing something stupid
and becoming a witness.

00:06:44.301 --> 00:06:45.344
Who else is there to blame?

00:06:48.472 --> 00:06:49.389
What about the men?

00:06:50.474 --> 00:06:52.434
Did you love Han Seol-ah so much

00:06:53.018 --> 00:06:54.102
but lacked the confidence?

00:06:55.187 --> 00:06:56.396
Was that why you killed them?

00:07:02.319 --> 00:07:03.153
Shut up.

00:07:03.237 --> 00:07:05.155
Don't run your mouth
when you don't know anything.

00:07:05.239 --> 00:07:07.616
Those bastards deserved to die!

00:07:11.203 --> 00:07:13.830
That damn doctor gaslit his patient

00:07:13.914 --> 00:07:15.666
and took out a life insurance policy.

00:07:17.125 --> 00:07:18.794
The bastard used Seol-ah's past trauma!

00:07:19.294 --> 00:07:20.128
LIFE INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

00:07:24.049 --> 00:07:25.550
POLICYHOLDER: CHOI YOUNG-HO

00:07:34.810 --> 00:07:36.687
Seol-ah canceled the policy

00:07:37.521 --> 00:07:39.231
because she was afraid
something bad might happen,

00:07:39.314 --> 00:07:41.608
but that bastard just wouldn't give up.

00:07:42.234 --> 00:07:44.820
He was nothing but a junkie,
sticking needles in his arm.

00:08:02.629 --> 00:08:04.548
I saved Seol-ah

00:08:05.132 --> 00:08:07.175
from that piece of shit, Choi Young-ho!

00:08:08.343 --> 00:08:09.636
Why did you kill Yoon Seung-jae?

00:08:10.804 --> 00:08:13.974
That pathetic guy was swayed
by Kim Yun-ji's words.

00:08:14.057 --> 00:08:15.642
Get out right now!

00:08:16.893 --> 00:08:18.687
You also took out
a life insurance policy, right?

00:08:19.646 --> 00:08:20.897
You'll regret it.

00:08:22.065 --> 00:08:22.899
"Seiren"?

00:08:23.984 --> 00:08:27.446
You know, mermaids that lured sailors
with their singing.

00:08:34.703 --> 00:08:37.581
Are you still worried
Seol-ah won't accept your proposal?

00:08:39.875 --> 00:08:40.709
Actually…

00:08:42.544 --> 00:08:44.504
I took out a life insurance policy
with Seol-ah as the beneficiary.

00:09:29.132 --> 00:09:31.301
He was a shallow bastard
who never trusted Seol-ah.

00:09:33.011 --> 00:09:35.514
He kept wondering
if she was only after his money.

00:09:37.474 --> 00:09:39.684
The only reason he refused to give her up…

00:09:41.895 --> 00:09:44.356
was that every man wanted her.

00:09:50.445 --> 00:09:52.656
He just wanted to keep her as his trophy!

00:09:55.909 --> 00:09:56.868
Don't you think it's better

00:09:57.994 --> 00:10:00.038
for bastards like him to just disappear
and leave the insurance payout behind?

00:10:16.805 --> 00:10:18.014
Who the hell do you think you are?

00:10:18.890 --> 00:10:20.517
What gives you the right?

00:10:21.685 --> 00:10:23.103
You obsessed over Han Seol-ah,

00:10:23.687 --> 00:10:26.481
labeled those men as trash,
and then you killed them!

00:10:27.065 --> 00:10:29.484
Your obsession and arrogance

00:10:30.277 --> 00:10:32.195
made Seol-ah's life a living hell.

00:10:33.488 --> 00:10:37.284
You saw her suffering with your own eyes
and did it anyway, you bastard!

00:10:50.839 --> 00:10:52.090
It doesn't matter…

00:10:55.051 --> 00:10:56.386
what you call me

00:10:57.429 --> 00:10:58.472
or what you think my place is.

00:11:06.771 --> 00:11:07.731
When you're underwater,

00:11:08.273 --> 00:11:11.318
every sound and struggle is drowned out.

00:11:12.569 --> 00:11:13.987
I'll make it quick.

00:11:20.452 --> 00:11:21.828
I think 20 kg is enough

00:11:21.912 --> 00:11:24.539
to keep your body underwater,
even as it decomposes.

00:11:29.252 --> 00:11:31.338
No, no, no.

00:11:31.421 --> 00:11:32.547
DETECTIVE GONG JOO-YOUNG

00:11:40.180 --> 00:11:41.264
CHEONGUN, WHERE LIFE IS GOOD
WELCOME TO CHEONGUN CITY

00:11:51.733 --> 00:11:52.567
Go farther.

00:11:53.318 --> 00:11:54.402
All the way to the edge.

00:11:59.574 --> 00:12:00.408
Go ahead and shoot me.

00:12:01.409 --> 00:12:02.702
If you kill me,

00:12:02.786 --> 00:12:04.704
Seol-ah will find out you're the culprit.

00:12:05.747 --> 00:12:06.581
Seol-ah trusts me.

00:12:07.832 --> 00:12:09.251
I just need to get rid of you.

00:12:11.253 --> 00:12:12.420
Don't kid yourself, Do Eun-hyuk.

00:12:14.214 --> 00:12:15.840
She already suspects you.

00:12:16.383 --> 00:12:18.343
You have no idea

00:12:18.426 --> 00:12:20.136
what we endured together.

00:12:20.720 --> 00:12:21.555
We'll never

00:12:22.722 --> 00:12:24.432
abandon each other.

00:12:28.311 --> 00:12:31.189
You should've just told her how you felt.

00:12:31.856 --> 00:12:33.608
She didn't seem to be aware
of your feelings.

00:12:34.192 --> 00:12:35.569
Was staying near her

00:12:35.652 --> 00:12:37.821
and getting rid of every man
your only goal?

00:12:52.460 --> 00:12:54.754
I have no intention of becoming her man.

00:12:55.630 --> 00:12:56.756
I'm just paying for my sins

00:12:58.174 --> 00:12:59.968
in my own way.

00:13:01.886 --> 00:13:02.887
Jump in.

00:13:03.471 --> 00:13:05.390
If you can't, I'll just shoot you.

00:13:06.850 --> 00:13:07.851
No!

00:13:08.476 --> 00:13:09.477
Eun-hyuk!

00:13:10.020 --> 00:13:10.854
Eun-hyuk.

00:13:11.605 --> 00:13:12.856
Eun-hyuk, please don't do this.

00:13:13.565 --> 00:13:15.400
Don't do it. Put it down.

00:13:16.026 --> 00:13:17.777
It's dangerous. Back away!

00:13:17.861 --> 00:13:18.737
Please stop.

00:13:18.820 --> 00:13:20.697
Put that down!

00:13:23.074 --> 00:13:23.908
Eun-hyuk.

00:13:23.992 --> 00:13:25.201
I said back away!

00:13:26.494 --> 00:13:28.204
It's me, Seol-ah.

00:13:33.293 --> 00:13:34.294
Please stop.

00:13:35.045 --> 00:13:36.630
That bastard destroyed us!

00:13:37.756 --> 00:13:39.299
Cha Woo-seok suspected you,

00:13:39.382 --> 00:13:40.675
and that's how it all started.

00:13:42.177 --> 00:13:44.179
That's how we got to this point!

00:13:49.392 --> 00:13:51.061
You killed people for me?

00:13:54.105 --> 00:13:56.316
Did you really think I'd want that?

00:13:59.069 --> 00:13:59.944
It's too late

00:14:01.112 --> 00:14:02.447
to turn back now.

00:14:08.328 --> 00:14:09.245
No!

00:14:32.060 --> 00:14:32.894
Seol-ah.

00:14:36.481 --> 00:14:37.315
Seol-ah.

00:14:37.941 --> 00:14:39.401
Seol-ah, stay with me.

00:14:39.484 --> 00:14:40.568
Seol-ah!

00:14:40.652 --> 00:14:41.569
Seol-ah.

00:14:52.789 --> 00:14:54.290
Seol-ah, stay with me.

00:14:56.126 --> 00:14:57.544
Why did you do that?!

00:15:00.046 --> 00:15:01.840
Seol-ah!

00:15:03.591 --> 00:15:05.844
-We need an ambulance!
-Don't move!

00:15:07.721 --> 00:15:08.805
What happened?

00:15:10.056 --> 00:15:11.015
She was shot.

00:15:11.099 --> 00:15:12.517
She's losing consciousness.

00:15:12.600 --> 00:15:14.185
Ms. Han, stay with me!

00:15:15.311 --> 00:15:16.146
Ms. Han!

00:15:35.623 --> 00:15:38.626
OPERATING CENTER

00:15:38.710 --> 00:15:40.378
SURGERY STATUS
HAN SEOL-**: IN SURGERY

00:16:07.071 --> 00:16:08.531
The surgery went well.

00:16:08.615 --> 00:16:11.117
There was some muscle damage,
so she'll need physical therapy,

00:16:11.618 --> 00:16:12.952
but she should heal over time.

00:16:14.829 --> 00:16:17.707
By some miracle,
the bullet didn't hit any major nerves,

00:16:17.791 --> 00:16:20.794
but once she comes out of anesthesia,
we'll monitor her for signs of paralysis

00:16:20.877 --> 00:16:24.088
and also administer painkillers
to ease the pain.

00:16:26.299 --> 00:16:27.425
Thank you.

00:16:27.509 --> 00:16:30.136
You should get treated as well.

00:16:48.822 --> 00:16:49.739
No!

00:16:57.997 --> 00:16:59.958
Why did you try to kill

00:17:00.708 --> 00:17:01.626
Cha Woo-seok?

00:17:13.721 --> 00:17:14.681
You recognize

00:17:15.807 --> 00:17:17.183
these people, don't you?

00:17:20.061 --> 00:17:21.312
Did Han Seol-ah order you

00:17:21.396 --> 00:17:23.273
to kill all of these men?

00:18:43.311 --> 00:18:44.896
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:18:47.774 --> 00:18:49.359
What are you doing at someone else's desk?

00:18:50.193 --> 00:18:53.363
Mr. Cha asked me to bring his laptop
and other things.

00:18:53.446 --> 00:18:55.865
It's like he's setting up an office
at the hospital.

00:18:55.949 --> 00:18:58.618
I told him to clear his head
and get some rest,

00:18:58.701 --> 00:18:59.953
but he refuses to listen.

00:19:00.578 --> 00:19:02.413
By the way, isn't it really shocking

00:19:02.497 --> 00:19:04.624
that the killer
is Ms. Han Seol-ah's friend?

00:19:04.707 --> 00:19:07.293
That's why they say we tend to miss
what's right in front of us.

00:19:07.377 --> 00:19:08.753
You never know
what someone is really like.

00:19:11.047 --> 00:19:14.300
You know, Mr. Cha got into a car accident,

00:19:14.384 --> 00:19:15.927
and he got shot twice.

00:19:16.010 --> 00:19:18.054
Don't you think our job is too dangerous?

00:19:18.137 --> 00:19:19.973
I was happy when I got the certification,

00:19:20.807 --> 00:19:23.309
but now I'm thinking
maybe I should switch jobs.

00:19:23.393 --> 00:19:26.145
Hey, do you think
Cha-cha got injured while working?

00:19:26.229 --> 00:19:29.357
-He didn't?
-Jeez. You have no clue, do you?

00:19:29.857 --> 00:19:32.402
He got injured
while trying to protect his woman.

00:19:33.152 --> 00:19:34.612
-What?
-What?

00:19:34.696 --> 00:19:35.530
No way.

00:19:35.613 --> 00:19:38.616
I thought this case
was like Basic Instinct,

00:19:38.700 --> 00:19:42.453
but it was actually
just a life-or-death romance movie.

00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:54.924
Did you hear?

00:19:55.758 --> 00:19:56.926
The doctor said

00:19:58.344 --> 00:19:59.595
if it hadn't been for you,

00:20:01.055 --> 00:20:02.932
the bullet would've gone through my heart.

00:20:03.975 --> 00:20:07.437
You saved me too, Woo-seok.

00:20:08.438 --> 00:20:09.897
Don't ever do that again.

00:20:10.815 --> 00:20:12.275
I never want to experience

00:20:13.067 --> 00:20:14.485
that kind of fear again.

00:20:18.364 --> 00:20:20.199
What happened to Eun-hyuk?

00:20:22.368 --> 00:20:24.162
It seems he's still refusing to talk.

00:20:25.204 --> 00:20:26.372
He knew me

00:20:27.123 --> 00:20:29.250
better than anyone else in the world.

00:20:30.585 --> 00:20:32.128
He was the only friend

00:20:32.628 --> 00:20:35.339
who stayed by my side with Suk-ji.

00:20:36.466 --> 00:20:39.677
He thought he was protecting you,

00:20:40.595 --> 00:20:41.888
but it was a misguided thought.

00:20:43.097 --> 00:20:44.474
I have to know.

00:20:45.058 --> 00:20:47.685
I need to hear why he did it.

00:20:49.103 --> 00:20:50.480
You need to recover first.

00:20:50.563 --> 00:20:52.482
Please tell the police

00:20:53.357 --> 00:20:55.693
that I'll turn myself in.

00:20:58.863 --> 00:21:00.198
I'm turning myself in.

00:21:03.326 --> 00:21:05.286
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:21:20.301 --> 00:21:25.098
TRUSTED POLICE, TOGETHER WITH THE PEOPLE
COMMITTED TO INTEGRITY AND TRANSPARENCY

00:21:25.848 --> 00:21:26.766
Seol-ah.

00:21:29.852 --> 00:21:30.812
Seol-ah!

00:21:32.438 --> 00:21:33.272
Why is she here?

00:21:33.856 --> 00:21:35.608
She turned herself in.

00:21:36.609 --> 00:21:38.444
She'll be investigated as the main culprit

00:21:38.528 --> 00:21:40.154
who ordered you to do what you did,

00:21:40.238 --> 00:21:41.697
so we don't need your statement anymore.

00:21:43.658 --> 00:21:45.910
No, leave Seol-ah alone.

00:21:47.370 --> 00:21:48.246
It was me.

00:21:48.329 --> 00:21:49.956
I killed them all!

00:21:50.623 --> 00:21:52.542
Seol-ah had nothing to do with it!

00:21:53.126 --> 00:21:55.711
Seol-ah doesn't know anything!

00:21:57.505 --> 00:21:59.298
She's innocent!

00:22:00.883 --> 00:22:02.468
Seol-ah didn't do it!

00:22:06.055 --> 00:22:07.640
She didn't know about any of it!

00:22:19.318 --> 00:22:21.946
What exactly
do you hope to gain from all this?

00:22:22.530 --> 00:22:25.658
Let me confront Do Eun-hyuk.

00:22:26.242 --> 00:22:27.076
If you do,

00:22:28.327 --> 00:22:29.912
do you think he'll talk?

00:22:32.290 --> 00:22:33.124
Probably.

00:22:34.792 --> 00:22:36.419
Because that's how he can protect her.

00:22:41.591 --> 00:22:42.758
Do Eun-hyuk says he'll confess.

00:22:44.010 --> 00:22:45.761
He wants Ms. Han released.

00:23:19.170 --> 00:23:22.006
How did you find out
Paek Jun-beom was Lee Su-ho?

00:23:32.725 --> 00:23:34.727
When I followed him to the villa,

00:23:36.479 --> 00:23:37.813
I got chills.

00:23:39.523 --> 00:23:41.943
The house that looked exactly the way
Lee Su-ho had described it.

00:23:43.152 --> 00:23:44.987
His one-sided smile.

00:23:46.364 --> 00:23:48.616
The way he was left-handed and his gait.

00:23:49.450 --> 00:23:51.160
-Surprise!
-Surprise!

00:23:52.536 --> 00:23:54.205
-What's all this?
-Happy birthday.

00:23:54.288 --> 00:23:55.873
Thank you.

00:23:56.791 --> 00:23:58.167
Happy birthday.

00:24:01.754 --> 00:24:02.838
But more importantly,

00:24:03.798 --> 00:24:05.466
it was the way he looked at Seol-ah.

00:24:07.301 --> 00:24:08.636
It bothered me from the start

00:24:09.637 --> 00:24:11.055
and somehow felt familiar.

00:24:21.315 --> 00:24:22.858
I just needed to confirm one last thing.

00:24:42.336 --> 00:24:43.671
The moment I confirmed his allergy,

00:24:45.172 --> 00:24:47.216
I knew that Seol-ah
also figured out who he was.

00:24:49.552 --> 00:24:51.554
And I could guess where they were headed.

00:25:17.621 --> 00:25:18.831
Get away from me!

00:25:36.974 --> 00:25:37.975
INDUSTRIAL CIRCUIT BREAKER

00:26:49.463 --> 00:26:52.133
She would've been in danger
if I hadn't gone there.

00:26:53.467 --> 00:26:54.718
That wasn't murder.

00:26:56.262 --> 00:26:57.972
I was protecting Seol-ah.

00:27:13.362 --> 00:27:14.572
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

00:27:15.948 --> 00:27:17.408
From study abroad expenses

00:27:17.491 --> 00:27:20.661
to underwater equipment and studio rent,

00:27:20.744 --> 00:27:24.373
why did Chair Kim Sun-ae
financially support you

00:27:24.957 --> 00:27:25.875
for over ten years?

00:27:27.960 --> 00:27:29.420
What did you do for her in return?

00:27:32.089 --> 00:27:33.757
I let her borrow my name.

00:27:33.841 --> 00:27:36.010
She made artwork transactions
under my name.

00:27:37.344 --> 00:27:38.888
So you just let her borrow your name--

00:27:38.971 --> 00:27:40.931
I killed Chair Kim too.

00:27:46.604 --> 00:27:48.397
She exploited Seol-ah
whenever it suited her,

00:27:48.481 --> 00:27:50.357
but when trouble came up,

00:27:51.442 --> 00:27:52.485
she tried to fire her.

00:28:04.955 --> 00:28:06.165
I think he's hiding something.

00:28:29.063 --> 00:28:31.440
I confessed that I was behind everything,

00:28:31.524 --> 00:28:32.900
so let Seol-ah go.

00:28:32.983 --> 00:28:34.485
She didn't know anything.

00:28:36.529 --> 00:28:37.905
Please let us talk alone.

00:28:37.988 --> 00:28:39.031
I have nothing to say.

00:28:39.114 --> 00:28:40.199
Do Eun-hyuk.

00:28:40.282 --> 00:28:41.367
Get her out of here.

00:28:41.450 --> 00:28:43.452
If not, I'll refuse to give a statement.

00:28:47.665 --> 00:28:49.875
You should leave for now.

00:28:52.211 --> 00:28:53.837
You said you did it for me.

00:28:55.589 --> 00:28:57.758
But you can't even look me in the eye.

00:28:57.841 --> 00:28:58.842
I said get out!

00:29:23.617 --> 00:29:24.660
Are you okay?

00:29:24.743 --> 00:29:26.745
They can't talk face-to-face.

00:29:26.829 --> 00:29:28.163
Do Eun-hyuk is adamantly refusing.

00:29:29.039 --> 00:29:30.708
He doesn't want Seol-ah
to see the worst of him.

00:29:38.591 --> 00:29:41.093
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

00:29:42.595 --> 00:29:45.514
You didn't hurt your stomach,
so keep eating throughout the day

00:29:45.598 --> 00:29:47.099
so you can heal quickly.

00:29:47.975 --> 00:29:48.809
Not in the mood?

00:29:51.228 --> 00:29:53.147
Do you want to wash your hair?
I saw a shampoo room.

00:29:53.230 --> 00:29:55.190
It's hard to do with one arm, right?

00:29:56.233 --> 00:29:57.067
Suk-ji.

00:29:57.943 --> 00:29:58.777
Yeah?

00:29:59.570 --> 00:30:01.030
Why aren't you asking me anything?

00:30:03.240 --> 00:30:04.199
To be honest,

00:30:05.367 --> 00:30:06.952
I still can't believe it.

00:30:07.828 --> 00:30:10.164
How could our childhood friend
do something like that?

00:30:10.247 --> 00:30:11.915
I thought about
grabbing that jerk by the neck

00:30:11.999 --> 00:30:15.294
or killing him with my own hands,

00:30:16.211 --> 00:30:17.463
but I had something more important to do.

00:30:18.505 --> 00:30:19.632
I have to take care of you.

00:30:33.520 --> 00:30:34.480
You're early.

00:30:34.563 --> 00:30:36.023
I thought you'd be coming
later in the evening.

00:30:36.982 --> 00:30:38.859
I took the day off,

00:30:38.942 --> 00:30:41.320
and Ms. Hwang has to go back to the bar.

00:30:41.904 --> 00:30:43.197
I hired a part-timer for the day.

00:30:44.198 --> 00:30:45.491
Oh, I see.

00:30:46.325 --> 00:30:49.119
But the owner should be there,

00:30:49.203 --> 00:30:50.454
so you can go.

00:30:51.121 --> 00:30:52.498
You came because you missed Seol-ah,
didn't you?

00:30:59.713 --> 00:31:00.923
I was worried too.

00:31:13.185 --> 00:31:14.728
He confessed,

00:31:15.312 --> 00:31:16.980
and the evidence checks out,

00:31:17.773 --> 00:31:19.775
but his motive for killing Chair Kim
seems weak.

00:31:19.858 --> 00:31:23.737
Maybe Chair Kim
had something on Do Eun-hyuk too.

00:31:23.821 --> 00:31:26.949
The amount is way too big to be
just payment for using someone's name.

00:31:27.032 --> 00:31:27.866
Ju Hyun-su.

00:31:28.575 --> 00:31:29.868
He was Chair Kim's lackey.

00:31:29.952 --> 00:31:31.537
He must have some connection
with Do Eun-hyuk.

00:31:36.792 --> 00:31:38.711
I can dry my own hair.

00:31:38.794 --> 00:31:40.838
But it's hard to do with one hand.

00:31:40.921 --> 00:31:42.881
I can ask a nurse for help.

00:31:43.757 --> 00:31:45.217
Just trust me.

00:31:45.300 --> 00:31:48.011
I did my younger sister's hair
all the time.

00:31:48.095 --> 00:31:50.305
It's not that I don't trust you.

00:31:51.473 --> 00:31:52.725
Are you shy?

00:31:54.184 --> 00:31:55.018
No.

00:31:56.520 --> 00:31:57.438
Go ahead, then.

00:32:16.707 --> 00:32:18.500
I should've offered to wash your hair too.

00:32:18.584 --> 00:32:19.460
No, it's…

00:32:28.719 --> 00:32:29.845
You're done now, right?

00:32:30.512 --> 00:32:31.472
No.

00:32:32.264 --> 00:32:33.307
Not yet.

00:32:43.150 --> 00:32:44.067
Do you think

00:32:44.902 --> 00:32:46.945
I'll be able to live a normal life again?

00:32:50.532 --> 00:32:52.743
Just like everyone else?

00:33:00.834 --> 00:33:01.710
Of course.

00:33:03.754 --> 00:33:04.755
How about

00:33:05.881 --> 00:33:07.257
we start things

00:33:08.509 --> 00:33:09.843
like a normal couple?

00:33:27.986 --> 00:33:29.321
Oh no!

00:33:29.404 --> 00:33:31.156
I'm sorry. Are you okay?

00:33:31.740 --> 00:33:33.242
My hand just…

00:33:33.325 --> 00:33:34.785
It's okay.

00:34:05.983 --> 00:34:08.652
EMERGENCY TRANSPORT

00:34:27.963 --> 00:34:29.923
I felt even more guilty toward Mr. Cha

00:34:30.465 --> 00:34:32.759
when I heard that guy had been arrested.

00:34:34.136 --> 00:34:36.138
I'm not trying to blame you.

00:34:37.097 --> 00:34:38.432
I'm just worried

00:34:39.057 --> 00:34:41.143
about how much
you must be beating yourself up.

00:34:42.019 --> 00:34:45.063
To be honest, I think I knew for a while

00:34:45.147 --> 00:34:46.398
that it was insurance fraud.

00:34:47.232 --> 00:34:48.567
But admitting that

00:34:48.650 --> 00:34:50.736
would mean that I let him get away.

00:34:50.819 --> 00:34:51.778
So I hid behind the verdict,

00:34:51.862 --> 00:34:54.615
acting like I'd done everything I could
and by the book,

00:34:54.698 --> 00:34:56.241
and being completely hypocritical.

00:34:56.325 --> 00:34:57.326
Honey.

00:34:57.826 --> 00:34:58.702
Sometimes,

00:35:00.037 --> 00:35:01.580
when I looked into Woo-seok's eyes,

00:35:01.663 --> 00:35:06.376
it felt like I was seeing the truth
I'd been avoiding.

00:35:09.046 --> 00:35:09.963
My poor husband.

00:35:11.465 --> 00:35:13.133
It must've been so hard for you.

00:35:16.094 --> 00:35:18.263
It's not too late to make things right.

00:35:19.181 --> 00:35:21.058
The only way I can make things right

00:35:21.683 --> 00:35:23.018
is to make sure that bastard Ju Hyun-su…

00:35:24.853 --> 00:35:26.396
receives the maximum sentence
under the law.

00:35:28.440 --> 00:35:29.399
That's it.

00:35:33.779 --> 00:35:34.905
You're finally going home.

00:35:35.781 --> 00:35:38.867
I have to stop by somewhere
before I go home.

00:35:41.536 --> 00:35:48.543
THE LATE CHA WOO-HEE
OCTOBER 8, 1993 - AUGUST 28, 2020

00:35:51.880 --> 00:35:53.715
I've been wanting to come here

00:35:55.008 --> 00:35:56.468
because I heard so much about her.

00:35:58.762 --> 00:36:00.222
It's become even harder to come here

00:36:01.223 --> 00:36:02.516
since catching Ju Hyun-su.

00:36:03.725 --> 00:36:05.978
It felt like I was the one
who should apologize

00:36:06.937 --> 00:36:07.980
instead of him.

00:36:08.939 --> 00:36:10.774
I think what your sister wants to hear

00:36:12.067 --> 00:36:14.903
is for you to say that you're okay now.

00:36:15.779 --> 00:36:18.865
I'm sure she'd want to see you smiling

00:36:19.408 --> 00:36:20.659
and living life to the fullest.

00:36:22.828 --> 00:36:24.871
I'll leave you
to spend some time with her.

00:36:24.955 --> 00:36:26.623
You should tell her things
you never got to say.

00:36:50.731 --> 00:36:51.732
Woo-hee.

00:36:57.988 --> 00:36:59.406
I'm…

00:37:02.325 --> 00:37:03.201
sorry.

00:37:14.296 --> 00:37:15.505
I should've come sooner.

00:37:47.954 --> 00:37:50.207
This is all I have
since I was in the hospital.

00:37:52.667 --> 00:37:53.502
Have you…

00:37:55.045 --> 00:37:56.797
visited Eun-hyuk?

00:37:57.964 --> 00:37:59.466
I think he's given up completely.

00:38:00.050 --> 00:38:03.553
He says he doesn't need a lawyer
and isn't going to appeal.

00:38:05.097 --> 00:38:06.431
At some point,

00:38:07.349 --> 00:38:08.975
he started acting strangely.

00:38:10.102 --> 00:38:11.228
And at some point,

00:38:12.062 --> 00:38:14.189
you became hostile toward me.

00:38:17.109 --> 00:38:18.110
I was afraid

00:38:19.528 --> 00:38:21.488
that he might've done something

00:38:21.988 --> 00:38:23.281
and wondered what he was up to.

00:38:24.199 --> 00:38:26.493
I was anxious and scared,

00:38:27.702 --> 00:38:29.579
so I lashed out at you.

00:38:30.247 --> 00:38:32.290
I told myself that everything
would be okay if you were gone

00:38:32.374 --> 00:38:33.875
and that you were behind it all.

00:38:35.335 --> 00:38:36.795
I wasn't with Eun-hyuk the whole day

00:38:38.296 --> 00:38:40.507
when Seung-jae's accident happened.

00:38:42.217 --> 00:38:44.886
I lied to the police

00:38:46.012 --> 00:38:48.348
and showed them
the food delivery receipt and photo,

00:38:48.932 --> 00:38:49.766
but Eun-hyuk…

00:38:51.226 --> 00:38:52.894
He knew I was giving a false statement,

00:38:54.437 --> 00:38:55.730
but he didn't say a word.

00:38:58.650 --> 00:39:00.026
I was hoping it was you.

00:39:00.610 --> 00:39:01.444
It was Han Seol-ah.

00:39:01.528 --> 00:39:03.196
That woman killed her.

00:39:03.280 --> 00:39:04.906
That's why I called in the tip

00:39:06.241 --> 00:39:07.409
to the police.

00:39:08.535 --> 00:39:09.452
I'm sorry.

00:39:11.329 --> 00:39:12.414
I shouldn't have done that.

00:39:13.874 --> 00:39:15.041
Eun-hye.

00:39:15.125 --> 00:39:16.793
You need to get it together.

00:39:17.377 --> 00:39:19.129
Things won't be easy,

00:39:19.713 --> 00:39:20.672
but you have to stay strong.

00:39:21.173 --> 00:39:22.215
He's…

00:39:23.425 --> 00:39:25.510
the only family I have left.

00:39:25.594 --> 00:39:27.637
I hate him to death,

00:39:28.346 --> 00:39:29.306
but I feel sorry for him.

00:39:32.434 --> 00:39:33.560
He wants you to visit him.

00:39:36.021 --> 00:39:37.522
He's still only looking for you…

00:39:39.733 --> 00:39:42.777
even though his life is in ruins.

00:40:20.815 --> 00:40:21.691
So…

00:40:22.943 --> 00:40:24.778
are you finally ready now?

00:40:28.240 --> 00:40:30.909
I know there's something
you have to tell me.

00:40:34.663 --> 00:40:35.997
That's why I asked you to come.

00:40:44.422 --> 00:40:46.174
Where did it all go wrong?

00:40:47.759 --> 00:40:49.719
How did it come to this?

00:40:51.805 --> 00:40:53.181
Bit by bit,

00:40:55.058 --> 00:40:56.393
as I recalled everything,

00:40:57.519 --> 00:40:58.770
I realized which day it was.

00:40:59.437 --> 00:41:01.690
It was the day I desperately wished

00:41:02.565 --> 00:41:04.484
I'd just die.

00:41:08.905 --> 00:41:10.573
The small hand you held out to me…

00:41:10.657 --> 00:41:11.533
Do Eun-hyuk, get up.

00:41:17.038 --> 00:41:18.456
…was my salvation

00:41:19.416 --> 00:41:20.959
and reason to live.

00:41:23.920 --> 00:41:25.130
I wanted to live.

00:41:29.217 --> 00:41:31.094
I just wanted to live.

00:41:31.594 --> 00:41:34.389
-Come here, you little bastard!
-Get away from me!

00:41:35.307 --> 00:41:37.017
-You moron!
-Go away!

00:41:50.322 --> 00:41:51.948
I just wanted to live.

00:41:54.284 --> 00:41:55.994
But my father died,

00:41:57.412 --> 00:41:58.997
and his death was ruled an accident.

00:41:59.664 --> 00:42:01.666
Nobody knew it was me who did it,

00:42:02.876 --> 00:42:04.336
but I think my mom knew.

00:42:06.087 --> 00:42:07.380
Where did I put it?

00:42:10.675 --> 00:42:12.344
GW LIFE INSURANCE
INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

00:42:13.219 --> 00:42:14.137
Mom!

00:42:15.555 --> 00:42:16.973
Mom.

00:42:17.057 --> 00:42:17.932
Mom!

00:42:19.893 --> 00:42:21.561
Mom, where are you going?!

00:42:21.644 --> 00:42:22.604
Mom!

00:42:23.730 --> 00:42:25.899
She took off
with my father's death benefit…

00:42:27.734 --> 00:42:29.152
and never came back.

00:42:33.198 --> 00:42:34.449
That's when I learned…

00:42:36.326 --> 00:42:37.494
you can make money

00:42:38.536 --> 00:42:40.205
when someone dies,

00:42:40.872 --> 00:42:41.915
and how death

00:42:42.999 --> 00:42:44.709
can be quietly covered up.

00:42:47.337 --> 00:42:48.838
Your parents

00:42:50.173 --> 00:42:52.050
got their insurance through my mom.

00:42:55.345 --> 00:42:57.972
You knew about that?

00:43:00.016 --> 00:43:01.309
It was me.

00:43:02.227 --> 00:43:03.645
I was the one who started the fire.

00:43:13.613 --> 00:43:14.614
That can't be.

00:43:15.365 --> 00:43:18.785
I remember holding the lighter.

00:43:22.789 --> 00:43:24.082
You had passed out.

00:43:30.630 --> 00:43:32.298
Seol-ah, wake up.

00:43:32.382 --> 00:43:33.550
Wake up.

00:44:13.465 --> 00:44:14.382
It wasn't you.

00:44:15.508 --> 00:44:16.468
It was me.

00:44:17.469 --> 00:44:19.387
I thought that
if you collected the payout,

00:44:21.055 --> 00:44:22.432
your parents' sacrifice

00:44:23.892 --> 00:44:26.019
wouldn't be in vain.

00:44:28.438 --> 00:44:32.692
I watched you suffer from a false memory
all these years,

00:44:33.693 --> 00:44:35.153
but I didn't have the courage to tell you.

00:44:36.654 --> 00:44:38.781
I became a monster

00:44:40.241 --> 00:44:41.868
the moment I caused my father's death,

00:44:42.994 --> 00:44:44.704
and I couldn't approach you any further

00:44:45.622 --> 00:44:47.624
after setting your house on fire.

00:44:48.875 --> 00:44:51.419
Remember what you said at Suk-ji's bar?

00:44:52.003 --> 00:44:53.129
You thought

00:44:54.047 --> 00:44:56.049
we'd grow up to be special to each other.

00:44:58.426 --> 00:44:59.385
Hearing that…

00:45:01.930 --> 00:45:03.515
made me so happy…

00:45:06.017 --> 00:45:07.143
yet sad at the same time.

00:45:10.396 --> 00:45:13.358
I ruined our fate with my own hands.

00:45:35.255 --> 00:45:37.549
Chair Kim saw everything.

00:45:38.341 --> 00:45:39.384
And after that,

00:45:40.426 --> 00:45:41.886
I became her lapdog.

00:45:53.439 --> 00:45:54.816
She knew

00:45:55.567 --> 00:45:57.443
what I was most afraid of.

00:45:59.362 --> 00:46:00.947
Ju Hyun-su will be out soon.

00:46:01.030 --> 00:46:03.324
Take care of that bastard quietly first.

00:46:03.408 --> 00:46:04.867
If you don't,

00:46:04.951 --> 00:46:08.246
I'll make sure she finds out
about the secret

00:46:08.329 --> 00:46:10.081
you're so desperate to keep from her.

00:46:33.438 --> 00:46:34.772
I was behind everything.

00:46:36.065 --> 00:46:37.984
So let go of your guilt

00:46:38.568 --> 00:46:39.777
and stop hurting.

00:46:41.070 --> 00:46:42.614
I'll take all the punishment.

00:46:43.197 --> 00:46:44.282
You once told me

00:46:44.782 --> 00:46:47.535
that no one gets to pick their parents
before they're born.

00:46:48.119 --> 00:46:49.996
You were abused and abandoned,

00:46:50.580 --> 00:46:52.165
and I became an orphan.

00:46:52.915 --> 00:46:54.500
But none of that was our fault.

00:46:55.251 --> 00:46:57.503
But how we chose to live afterward

00:46:58.212 --> 00:46:59.631
was entirely up to us.

00:47:00.923 --> 00:47:02.550
I was in a lot of pain,

00:47:02.634 --> 00:47:04.844
but I accepted the life I was given.

00:47:04.927 --> 00:47:08.598
You had so many chances
to make a different decision.

00:47:10.558 --> 00:47:12.060
By the time I realized that,

00:47:12.935 --> 00:47:14.145
it was too late.

00:47:14.854 --> 00:47:16.397
I had no choice

00:47:16.481 --> 00:47:18.232
but to continue down the path I'd been on.

00:47:19.359 --> 00:47:21.736
You're the one
who made me the most miserable.

00:47:28.368 --> 00:47:29.494
Seol-ah.

00:47:29.577 --> 00:47:30.745
Don't ever call me

00:47:32.246 --> 00:47:33.915
by my name again.

00:49:36.329 --> 00:49:41.959
DRAWING THE MIND

00:49:46.172 --> 00:49:47.882
DRAWING THE MIND: ART THERAPY PROGRAM
WITH NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:49:58.810 --> 00:50:01.270
-Hello, here's a gift for you.
-Hello.

00:50:06.651 --> 00:50:08.027
Mr. Cha.

00:50:08.110 --> 00:50:09.987
Chae-rin, how've you been?

00:50:11.030 --> 00:50:11.989
How are you feeling?

00:50:12.073 --> 00:50:13.699
I feel a lot better now.

00:50:14.242 --> 00:50:16.452
I came as a helper today.

00:50:17.286 --> 00:50:18.204
Think you can do a good job?

00:50:21.791 --> 00:50:23.709
I'm counting on you, Chae-rin.

00:50:23.793 --> 00:50:25.545
-Okay.
-Here, take this.

00:50:26.128 --> 00:50:26.963
How've you been?

00:50:39.517 --> 00:50:41.310
She's still in foster care, right?

00:50:42.311 --> 00:50:43.145
Yeah.

00:50:43.229 --> 00:50:45.064
She has to go to the hospital often,

00:50:45.815 --> 00:50:46.774
so it hasn't been easy.

00:50:54.282 --> 00:50:59.161
DRAWING THE MIND

00:50:59.245 --> 00:51:00.162
Okay, everyone.

00:51:00.246 --> 00:51:03.583
Today, we're going to create a new story.

00:51:03.666 --> 00:51:05.960
Leave the sad past behind,

00:51:06.043 --> 00:51:08.421
imagine the person you want to become,

00:51:08.504 --> 00:51:10.172
and let that imagination

00:51:10.840 --> 00:51:12.592
run free on the paper.

00:51:12.675 --> 00:51:14.385
-Okay!
-Okay!

00:51:14.969 --> 00:51:16.012
Then let's begin.

00:51:23.853 --> 00:51:24.687
Look at this.

00:51:34.196 --> 00:51:35.323
Try this too.

00:51:35.406 --> 00:51:37.408
Thank you, Chae-rin.

00:51:48.586 --> 00:51:50.421
So you like blue, huh?

00:51:50.504 --> 00:51:53.132
Yes, I like it
because it reminds me of the sky.

00:51:59.805 --> 00:52:00.973
That must've hurt.

00:52:05.436 --> 00:52:08.439
It doesn't hurt when I draw.

00:52:08.522 --> 00:52:10.608
I like drawing because it helps me
forget about the past.

00:52:11.192 --> 00:52:12.068
Does it?

00:52:13.235 --> 00:52:14.403
The same goes for me.

00:52:14.487 --> 00:52:16.197
That's why I drew a lot

00:52:16.280 --> 00:52:18.491
and made a lot of wood carvings.

00:52:19.075 --> 00:52:20.993
Then I want to keep drawing too.

00:52:21.077 --> 00:52:22.620
It's so much fun.

00:52:23.204 --> 00:52:24.205
You should.

00:52:25.206 --> 00:52:27.124
And someday,
we can hold an exhibition together.

00:52:27.208 --> 00:52:28.376
Really?

00:52:31.128 --> 00:52:32.046
I promise.

00:53:00.282 --> 00:53:02.952
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:53:03.035 --> 00:53:04.286
The SIU

00:53:04.912 --> 00:53:06.914
never makes a move without data

00:53:06.998 --> 00:53:09.917
because lies always leave a trace.

00:53:12.003 --> 00:53:13.129
Are you kidding me?

00:53:13.212 --> 00:53:16.257
I told you I can't move my neck
or use my hands.

00:53:16.340 --> 00:53:17.466
Are you refusing to pay?

00:53:18.050 --> 00:53:21.470
Mr. Koo, your acting is so bad
that I can't get into it.

00:53:21.554 --> 00:53:23.347
-Got it. Let's try again.
-Okay.

00:53:25.933 --> 00:53:26.976
You punk!

00:53:27.059 --> 00:53:28.894
You little jerk.

00:53:28.978 --> 00:53:30.396
How dare you accuse me of lying?

00:53:30.479 --> 00:53:32.940
I bet people tell you all the time
that you're rude.

00:53:33.024 --> 00:53:35.359
How dare you say that
when you have no evidence?

00:53:35.443 --> 00:53:37.862
You've been waiting to say that,
haven't you?

00:53:37.945 --> 00:53:40.072
Mr. Cha, I'm too scared to continue.

00:53:40.156 --> 00:53:41.991
You're such a wimp.

00:53:42.074 --> 00:53:43.701
It's scarier in real life.

00:53:45.411 --> 00:53:46.746
Oh, jeez!

00:53:48.914 --> 00:53:50.541
You've still got quick reflexes, huh?

00:53:50.624 --> 00:53:51.959
Come on, Cha-cha.

00:53:52.043 --> 00:53:53.711
This is just practice.

00:53:53.794 --> 00:53:55.629
Why are you treating it
like it's the real thing?

00:53:55.713 --> 00:53:57.131
See?

00:53:57.214 --> 00:53:59.216
People who commit fraud
can lie with words,

00:53:59.300 --> 00:54:00.509
but their body never lies.

00:54:01.844 --> 00:54:03.179
As expected of Grim Reaper Cha.

00:54:03.804 --> 00:54:04.722
I need to write this down.

00:54:08.809 --> 00:54:10.895
Mr. Cha, you have a guest.

00:54:11.687 --> 00:54:12.605
Me?

00:54:21.614 --> 00:54:22.948
Ju Hyun-su's verdict is in.

00:54:24.200 --> 00:54:25.159
I saw the article.

00:54:25.951 --> 00:54:27.328
He got 15 years.

00:54:28.579 --> 00:54:29.455
I'm sorry.

00:54:30.289 --> 00:54:32.083
That was the maximum sentence
under the law.

00:54:37.379 --> 00:54:38.631
I know it's too late,

00:54:39.298 --> 00:54:41.050
but I didn't think
I had the right to apologize

00:54:41.634 --> 00:54:43.594
until Ju Hyun-su's verdict came in.

00:54:47.139 --> 00:54:49.350
I made you
face that long, hard fight alone.

00:54:51.060 --> 00:54:52.603
And for that, I have no excuses to make

00:54:53.646 --> 00:54:54.730
as a detective and a human being.

00:55:01.195 --> 00:55:02.113
Thank you…

00:55:03.739 --> 00:55:05.157
for the apology.

00:55:11.997 --> 00:55:13.499
Detective Gong told me

00:55:13.582 --> 00:55:16.544
you're on a case involving a death benefit
of more than four billion won.

00:55:17.211 --> 00:55:18.337
I am, but what about it?

00:55:19.380 --> 00:55:20.673
These are the call logs
of those linked to the deceased.

00:55:22.091 --> 00:55:23.551
There's one number that kept appearing.

00:55:29.140 --> 00:55:30.766
CALL LOG

00:56:01.130 --> 00:56:02.339
You're here.

00:56:02.423 --> 00:56:04.258
I got some groceries on my way here.

00:56:05.634 --> 00:56:06.635
Cucumbers,

00:56:07.887 --> 00:56:08.721
eggs,

00:56:10.472 --> 00:56:11.390
carrots,

00:56:12.057 --> 00:56:13.017
and last but not least,

00:56:14.393 --> 00:56:15.394
some fruit.

00:56:15.477 --> 00:56:17.354
I noticed you were out of fruit.

00:56:17.438 --> 00:56:19.440
You're very observant.

00:56:19.523 --> 00:56:21.358
Well, it comes with the job.

00:56:22.902 --> 00:56:25.070
-Did you make stew?
-Yes. Do you want a taste?

00:56:32.494 --> 00:56:33.495
What do you think?

00:56:38.334 --> 00:56:39.376
-I have a weapon.
-I was kidding.

00:56:40.461 --> 00:56:41.879
-It was a joke.
-I have a weapon.

00:56:41.962 --> 00:56:43.714
I was just messing with you.

00:56:44.215 --> 00:56:46.258
It's really good. It's seasoned perfectly.

00:56:48.427 --> 00:56:51.388
I never thought I'd find myself
making warm, home-cooked meals.

00:56:52.431 --> 00:56:54.683
You were too focused on work before.

00:56:55.267 --> 00:56:57.394
Take better care of yourself from now on.

00:56:59.313 --> 00:57:02.191
I don't think someone more of a workaholic
than me has the right to say that.

00:57:31.428 --> 00:57:32.554
Take this too.

00:57:36.183 --> 00:57:37.476
Han Seol-ah,

00:57:38.143 --> 00:57:40.729
you deserve to be much happier
than anyone else.

00:57:43.274 --> 00:57:44.525
Please let me…

00:57:46.402 --> 00:57:47.403
make that happen for you.

00:57:55.661 --> 00:57:56.912
I can't accept this.

00:57:58.580 --> 00:57:59.581
The truth is,

00:58:00.165 --> 00:58:01.625
I'm getting ready to study abroad.

00:58:02.293 --> 00:58:03.836
I want to study art therapy,

00:58:03.919 --> 00:58:06.880
which helps children heal through art.

00:58:08.132 --> 00:58:10.926
I don't know how long I'll be away.

00:58:28.110 --> 00:58:29.153
I still want you to accept this.

00:58:30.738 --> 00:58:31.989
I'm not stopping you from going.

00:58:32.740 --> 00:58:34.283
Do whatever you want.

00:58:36.243 --> 00:58:37.328
I'll wait.

00:58:39.246 --> 00:58:40.664
I can't make you do that.

00:58:40.748 --> 00:58:42.291
I'll take time off and visit you.

00:58:42.374 --> 00:58:44.043
If you want me to visit, I'll visit.

00:58:44.126 --> 00:58:45.836
If you want me to wait, I'll wait.

00:58:49.381 --> 00:58:50.466
You know what?

00:58:50.549 --> 00:58:51.842
Let's go together.

00:58:51.925 --> 00:58:53.177
I can go with you.

00:58:53.761 --> 00:58:56.805
I can take a sabbatical
and take care of you while you study.

00:59:02.436 --> 00:59:03.645
Whatever choice you make…

00:59:06.148 --> 00:59:07.274
I'll be by your side.

00:59:16.950 --> 00:59:18.202
Just trust me for once.

00:59:20.454 --> 00:59:21.497
I already do.

00:59:23.665 --> 00:59:25.626
But you were planning on
leaving me behind?

00:59:29.546 --> 00:59:31.298
It seemed too selfish of me.

00:59:32.383 --> 00:59:33.384
You can be selfish

00:59:34.635 --> 00:59:35.886
with me.

00:59:36.512 --> 00:59:37.930
You can be stubborn and throw tantrums.

00:59:39.848 --> 00:59:40.891
Whatever you do,

00:59:41.767 --> 00:59:43.102
I'll take it all.

00:59:45.104 --> 00:59:46.230
We only

00:59:47.731 --> 00:59:49.024
have each other now.

00:59:50.109 --> 00:59:53.862
I'll be your mother, father,
older brother, and younger brother.

00:59:56.031 --> 00:59:57.032
I'll be your everything.

01:00:25.602 --> 01:00:28.230
This painting right here
has been on display

01:00:28.313 --> 01:00:31.400
in the Royal Auction exhibition hall
for many years.

01:00:31.984 --> 01:00:38.240
The world often calls people
who quietly bear their burdens monsters.

01:00:38.991 --> 01:00:40.659
This seiren here

01:00:40.742 --> 01:00:43.203
also represents
temptation and destruction.

01:00:44.913 --> 01:00:46.999
But perhaps the real monster

01:00:47.082 --> 01:00:49.251
is the prejudice we direct at others.

01:00:49.960 --> 01:00:51.837
People who refuse to see the truth

01:00:52.421 --> 01:00:55.340
and instead are quick to judge others

01:00:55.841 --> 01:00:59.470
are the ones who pull them
deeper beneath the surface.

01:01:01.722 --> 01:01:05.267
To me, this seiren now seems less
like a creature that harms others

01:01:06.185 --> 01:01:09.855
and more like a survivor
who kept her voice alive

01:01:09.938 --> 01:01:11.398
in the face of prejudice.

01:01:14.193 --> 01:01:17.529
If you happen to be navigating
such waters right now,

01:01:18.530 --> 01:01:19.364
I truly hope

01:01:20.199 --> 01:01:23.243
you don't lose your own voice.

01:01:24.828 --> 01:01:25.871
CHIEF AUCTIONEER HAN SEOL-AH

01:01:36.256 --> 01:01:37.090
Sang-mi,

01:01:38.342 --> 01:01:40.052
I'll leave this with you.

01:01:40.135 --> 01:01:41.303
Okay, Ms. Han.

01:01:42.346 --> 01:01:43.680
Thank you.

01:01:43.764 --> 01:01:45.974
Thank you all for everything.

01:01:46.058 --> 01:01:47.768
Can we still keep in touch with you?

01:01:47.851 --> 01:01:48.810
Of course.

01:01:50.020 --> 01:01:51.355
Take care.

01:02:49.955 --> 01:02:50.956
There was a time

01:02:52.207 --> 01:02:54.084
when the world called a woman a witch.

01:02:56.587 --> 01:02:58.672
People condemned her too easily…

01:02:59.214 --> 01:03:00.257
A FAMILY
BY HAN JIN-WOO

01:03:00.340 --> 01:03:01.758
…and cast stones at her without thinking.

01:03:04.177 --> 01:03:05.429
Which side are you on?

01:03:07.222 --> 01:03:08.557
Are you the one being pelted,

01:03:09.057 --> 01:03:10.225
or the one throwing stones?

01:03:12.769 --> 01:03:14.187
The truth is often cruel,

01:03:14.896 --> 01:03:16.064
and some scars

01:03:16.982 --> 01:03:18.483
never fade.

01:03:21.278 --> 01:03:22.654
Regardless, don't give up.

01:03:24.197 --> 01:03:25.699
Keep loving anyway.

01:03:28.076 --> 01:03:29.911
My witch still cries sometimes,

01:03:31.121 --> 01:03:32.247
but we're together.

01:03:34.416 --> 01:03:35.751
There's no salvation.

01:03:37.419 --> 01:03:38.587
There's only the choice

01:03:39.588 --> 01:03:40.672
to hold each other's hands

01:03:41.590 --> 01:03:42.674
and never let go.

01:04:50.325 --> 01:04:52.327
Subtitle: Jenny Kim